    "updated_at": "2014-09-11T01:54:59Z",
    "body": "You can implement the same thing by creating a socket file (or named pipe on Windows) and listening to it to achieve the same thing, you can reference to how Atom editor did it:\nhttps://github.com/atom/atom/blob/master/src/browser/atom-application.coffee#L17\n\nThere will be no built-in support for the `single-instance` feature in atom-shell because everything can be implemented with Node here.\n"
