    "created_at": "2015-09-06T22:22:28Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-09-06T22:22:28Z",
    "body": "I did as @paulcbetts asked and spun this into a isolated node module [here](https://www.npmjs.com/package/monogamous). You can put it as a kind of evented facade in front of your normal main process bootstrap code.\nI have a usage example for electron and I am using it on my electron app.\n@f0zi if you subscribe to its `reboot` event you can just call `myElectronWindow.focus()` and it seems to Just Work (havent checked on windows yet but OSX works ok).\n"
