    "created_at": "2015-10-14T20:03:04Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-10-14T20:03:04Z",
    "body": "> There will be no built-in support for the single-instance feature in atom-shell because everything can be implemented with Node here.\n\nWe're actually seeing a compelling counter-example for this - `net.createServer` doesn't let you set the permissions of the pipe, which means that if users run an instance as Elevated Admin, further instances will see the pipe but fail to write to it, resulting in single-instance failing. While I'm totally up for sending PRs to monogamous, it seems like that it might be way easier to build this into Electron\n"
  },
